01:34.560 --> 01:35.720
I bet you love that.

01:36.920 --> 01:40.440
Sash can't move like this.
I like the way you move.

01:40.520 --> 01:44.760
- Are you really as awful as you seem?
- You have the best dreams, Jo.

01:46.320 --> 01:50.320
Mum, I was thinking,
maybe I could come back home?

01:50.400 --> 01:54.440
- To live.
- Really? Really, are you?

01:54.520 --> 01:55.960
I would be so happy.

02:08.720 --> 02:09.600
Finn!

02:10.880 --> 02:12.480
Finn!

02:13.480 --> 02:14.320
Rob?

02:21.920 --> 02:23.440
No, don't...

02:24.640 --> 02:26.240
Promise you'll never leave me.

02:28.200 --> 02:30.640
Rob, please don't do this.

02:45.680 --> 02:46.680
Rob...

02:48.400 --> 02:49.600
Why?

02:56.320 --> 02:57.600
Why are we back here?

02:57.680 --> 03:00.320
People don't just collapse
for no reason, do they?

03:00.400 --> 03:03.480
None of the tests are telling us
anything we don't already know.

03:05.600 --> 03:08.640
- Which is actually good news.
- How can that be good news?

03:08.720 --> 03:09.640
For Christ's sake!

03:11.320 --> 03:14.880
Have you been allowing yourself
to get stressed?

03:14.960 --> 03:19.160
Because if you have,
that's probably why you fainted.

03:20.360 --> 03:21.400
I think, Jo,

03:22.200 --> 03:25.080
